1
00:00:11,458 --> 00:00:13,750
[IRINA humming]

2
00:00:13,833 --> 00:00:17,125
So you're, uh, sure you know
what you're doing, miss?

3
00:00:17,208 --> 00:00:18,541
Cut me some slack, sweetheart.

4
00:00:18,625 --> 00:00:22,291
It's in the name, Irina
Jelavich, the Seductive Witch.

5
00:00:22,375 --> 00:00:24,666
You wanna kick, you came
to the right enchantress.

6
00:00:24,750 --> 00:00:27,125
Those silly little boys will
be knocked on their asses!

7
00:00:27,208 --> 00:00:29,708
You promise?

8
00:00:29,791 --> 00:00:31,375
Commander K, look out!

9
00:00:31,458 --> 00:00:33,583
Hey, we're fine with making
chocolates ourselves.

10
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:35,041
It's really no big deal.

11
00:00:35,125 --> 00:00:36,416
[IRINA]
Shush.

12
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:37,833
Just sit back, hun,

13
00:00:37,916 --> 00:00:39,625
and watch a master of the
dark arts strut her stuff.

14
00:00:39,708 --> 00:00:41,500
Um, that "stuff" looks rank.

15
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:46,250
[IRINA cackling]

16
00:01:50,166 --> 00:01:51,416
[MAEHARA]
No kidding?

17
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:53,041
You're giving this to me?

18
00:01:53,125 --> 00:01:55,125
Jerk. Got a problem?
I'll take 'em back!

19
00:01:55,208 --> 00:01:57,750
[MAEHARA]
No, no! I'm totally stoked!

20
00:01:57,833 --> 00:01:58,666
Oh, sweet!

21
00:01:58,750 --> 00:02:00,416
Yeah, don't get too excited.

22
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:03,666
Just consider it an apology
for all the crap I give you.

23
00:02:03,750 --> 00:02:07,500
[TOKA] Here ya go, fellas.
Happy Valentines Day.

24
00:02:07,583 --> 00:02:09,875
I know it's just because
you're nice, but wow, thanks!

25
00:02:09,958 --> 00:02:11,791
Where's Karasuma? Aw, c'mon.

26
00:02:11,875 --> 00:02:14,125
I really wanted to give
him these chocolates.

27
00:02:14,208 --> 00:02:16,625
Why's he gotta be gone today?

28
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:20,083
[SUGINO]
Woo!

29
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:21,666
[screams]

30
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:23,041
[SUGINO]
Yes! Yes! Yes!

31
00:02:23,125 --> 00:02:24,291
[KANZAKI chuckles]

32
00:02:24,375 --> 00:02:26,166
[KANZAKI]
I'm, uh, glad you like them.

33
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:27,750
Jeez, get a grip, dude.

34
00:02:27,833 --> 00:02:30,166
I know it's a dream
come true, but still.

35
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:31,208
Gah, these are so good!

36
00:02:31,291 --> 00:02:33,208
I'm gonna wolf down
the whole box!

37
00:02:33,291 --> 00:02:35,500
[KIMURA]
I know, right? Me, too!

38
00:02:35,583 --> 00:02:39,791
Are there anymore?
Please tell me you've got more.

39
00:02:39,875 --> 00:02:41,166
[gasps]

40
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:43,375
[BOTH] Chocolate. Chocolate.
Chocolate. Chocolate.

41
00:02:43,458 --> 00:02:45,000
[TOKA screams]

42
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:48,083
Was this supposed to happen?

43
00:02:48,166 --> 00:02:49,208
[OKUDA]
Hm?

44
00:02:49,291 --> 00:02:50,625
That's not good.

45
00:02:50,708 --> 00:02:52,125
The love potion
Professor Bitch made

46
00:02:52,208 --> 00:02:54,083
contains a highly
addictive compound!

47
00:02:54,166 --> 00:02:55,166
Do what now?!

48
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:56,041
Yes.

49
00:02:56,125 --> 00:02:58,166
These chocolates have the effect

50
00:02:58,250 --> 00:03:02,916
of making people...
crave... chocolate!

51
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Holy crap!

52
00:03:05,083 --> 00:03:06,541
[HINANO screams]

53
00:03:08,291 --> 00:03:10,916
[HINANO]
Uh! Get away from me!

54
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,166
[TOKA]
Is it just me,

55
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:20,250
or did Professor Bitch
not prepare us for this?

56
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:22,500
Whoa, whoa! Back off!
These are for me!

57
00:03:22,583 --> 00:03:23,541
[OKAJIMA]
Chocolate!

58
00:03:23,625 --> 00:03:24,875
Don't even try, pervert!

59
00:03:24,958 --> 00:03:26,125
And drop the act already

60
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:27,875
since nobody gave you
anything to begin with!

61
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:29,208
Go away! Hyah!

62
00:03:29,291 --> 00:03:32,250
This from Kanzaki!
Lay a hand on it and you die!

63
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:34,166
You're seriously protective
of your chocolate.

64
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:37,166
Damn right! I was gonna keep
it as a family heirloom.

65
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:39,625
But desperate times!

66
00:03:39,708 --> 00:03:42,833
Sugino! Don't tell me Kanzaki
was in on this, too!

67
00:03:42,916 --> 00:03:44,250
Nuh-uh.

68
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:47,458
I totally grabbed it from the
bargain aisle yesterday.

69
00:03:47,541 --> 00:03:49,125
[KANZAKI screams]

70
00:03:49,208 --> 00:03:51,208
I'm invincible!

71
00:03:51,291 --> 00:03:52,541
[NAGISA, MAEHARA]
Uh, what the hell?!

72
00:03:52,625 --> 00:03:55,166
What's worse? Zombies
or Sugino is beast mode?

73
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:57,125
Yeah, that would be his bug.

74
00:03:57,208 --> 00:03:59,500
Whenever Sugino reaches
peak excitement levels,

75
00:03:59,583 --> 00:04:00,875
he goes full-on berserker.

76
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:02,291
Huh. That's good to know.

77
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:03,583
--[crash]
--[SUGINO roars]

78
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:06,291
What do we do? We have
to rein the poor guy in!

79
00:04:06,375 --> 00:04:08,208
Little easier said than
done at the moment.

80
00:04:08,291 --> 00:04:11,541
[ALL]
Chocolate. Chocolate! Chocolate!

81
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:13,666
I've got it! Listen up!

82
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:16,500
You can have all the chocolate
you want if you stop Sugino!

83
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:21,916
[ALL yelling]

84
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,208
[NAKAMURA sighs]

85
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:24,750
'Least we bought ourselves
a little time, yeah?

86
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:27,375
It sounds like a battle
royale out there.

87
00:04:27,458 --> 00:04:29,791
Is there zombie juice
in the ones you gave me?

88
00:04:29,875 --> 00:04:32,000
Huh?! What is wrong with you?!

89
00:04:32,083 --> 00:04:34,208
Newsflash, jerkwad,
it's rude to ask a girl

90
00:04:34,291 --> 00:04:36,750
if she poisoned your
Valentine's present!

91
00:04:38,375 --> 00:04:40,750
[SUGINO howling]

92
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:41,875
[MAEHARA sighs]

93
00:04:41,958 --> 00:04:43,791
Man, yesterday was
a total cluster.

94
00:04:43,875 --> 00:04:46,416
Sorry for getting swept up
in the zombie rampage.

95
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:49,458
But thank goodness the
effects only last 24 hours.

96
00:04:49,541 --> 00:04:51,708
If only that were
true for Sugino.

97
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,833
[ISOGAI] What do you mean
you're transferring?!

98
00:04:53,916 --> 00:04:56,416
C'mon, Takebayashi,
you can't just leave!

99
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:58,166
Oh, I assure you, I can.

100
00:04:58,250 --> 00:04:59,625
[KOYAMA snickering]

101
00:04:59,708 --> 00:05:01,500
[NAGISA]
What are you guys talking about?

102
00:05:01,583 --> 00:05:03,375
[KAEDE]
And what's he doing here?

103
00:05:03,458 --> 00:05:05,125
[NAKAMURA]
Takebayashi is dropping E-class

104
00:05:05,208 --> 00:05:06,875
to join the paladins.

105
00:05:06,958 --> 00:05:08,291
Or as I like to put it,

106
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:11,000
spreading my wings and leaving
you losers in the dust.

107
00:05:11,083 --> 00:05:12,666
Way too good a deal to pass up.

108
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:14,083
[KARMA]
Spreading your wings, huh?

109
00:05:14,166 --> 00:05:16,125
More like flappin'
your dorsal fin.

110
00:05:16,208 --> 00:05:18,750
Explain to me why an elite
group of mage-warriors

111
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,958
would cherry pick a
nobody from this dump?

112
00:05:21,041 --> 00:05:22,916
Definitely something
suspicious here.

113
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,666
Maybe they want Koro-sensei--

114
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,250
Oh, right, my bad,
I meant to say Demon King.

115
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:28,333
[KAEDE gasps]

116
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:30,041
Someone should
review their priorities!

117
00:05:30,125 --> 00:05:31,958
We're supposed to be
in this together!

118
00:05:32,041 --> 00:05:34,208
[TAKEBAYASHI] Like when everyone
got all bent outta shape

119
00:05:34,291 --> 00:05:36,083
over a little chocolate?

120
00:05:36,166 --> 00:05:40,083
If I had any doubts before
yesterday, they're gone now.

121
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:42,416
This class is the
bottom of the barrel.

122
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,208
You can't really mean that.

123
00:05:44,291 --> 00:05:46,750
I have no choice
here but to secede.

124
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:49,750
Staying isn't going to win
the approval of my parents.

125
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:52,958
I want a future--
a chance to shine.

126
00:05:53,041 --> 00:05:54,625
And most importantly...

127
00:05:54,708 --> 00:05:56,541
...Valentine's Day Chocolate.

128
00:05:56,625 --> 00:05:58,250
From upwardly mobile paladin!

129
00:05:58,333 --> 00:05:59,833
That's your main motivation?!

130
00:05:59,916 --> 00:06:01,500
You really need to calm down.

131
00:06:01,583 --> 00:06:04,083
We're gonna need a better
reason than that.

132
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:05,458
[TAKEBAYASHI]
You guys are popular.

133
00:06:05,541 --> 00:06:07,666
You wouldn't understand.

134
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:08,958
[ISOGAI, MAEHARA]
Uh?

135
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:11,583
Of all the postcards
on Shinjuku Promenade,

136
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:13,416
mine were the very
last ones to be taken!

137
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:15,375
What are you doing?!
Don't share that kind of thing!

138
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:17,625
No one would've known
if you hadn't said it!

139
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:18,791
Would've known what?!

140
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:20,708
[TAKEBAYASHI]
Koro-Q.

141
00:06:20,791 --> 00:06:22,333
Let me go, damn it!

142
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:25,291
I'm joining the paladins
and getting chocolate for...

143
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:26,750
Okay. Now what?

144
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,208
That should hold him
for a little while.

145
00:06:28,291 --> 00:06:31,291
I-I can't believe after
everything we've been through...

146
00:06:31,375 --> 00:06:33,708
'S gotta be something'll
make him wanna stay.

147
00:06:33,791 --> 00:06:36,875
We can't defeat Koro-sensei
unless we do it as a group.

148
00:06:36,958 --> 00:06:39,916
I have the perfect idea.

149
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,291
Lemme go!

150
00:06:41,375 --> 00:06:43,291
[GIRLS]
Hello, master!

151
00:06:43,375 --> 00:06:48,375
If it's maids you want,
there are plenty... right here!

152
00:06:48,458 --> 00:06:49,541
[OKAJIMA]
We've died and gone to heaven!

153
00:06:49,625 --> 00:06:50,958
[SUGINO]
Kanzaki!

154
00:06:51,041 --> 00:06:54,250
Ugh. I feel so gross.
Why does anyone dress like this?

155
00:06:54,333 --> 00:06:55,833
Don't look. It's creepy.

156
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:58,000
Uh. Yeah. What she said.

157
00:06:58,083 --> 00:06:59,916
I'm hating how well
you pull this off.

158
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,750
[KARMA snickers]

159
00:07:03,208 --> 00:07:06,458
[TOKA] So anything master
wants in particular?

160
00:07:06,541 --> 00:07:08,625
Just say the word and
your wish is our command.

161
00:07:08,708 --> 00:07:10,166
What have you done with Yada?!

162
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:12,583
This is straight up ero-tech
from Professor Bitch herself.

163
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:15,666
Guaranteed to keep
any man where he is.

164
00:07:17,583 --> 00:07:20,000
[OKAJIMA, MAEHARA, TOKA]
So why isn't it working?!

165
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:24,041
[TAKEBAYASHI] Being my maid
is no simple matter!

166
00:07:24,125 --> 00:07:28,625
To wit, first she must
relinquish one whole dimension!

167
00:07:28,708 --> 00:07:31,166
There were boobs in his face
and he didn't even flinch?!

168
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:32,750
What evil magic is this?!

169
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,958
[TOKA]
Koro-Q!

170
00:07:35,041 --> 00:07:37,291
Perk up. No point
bein' so negative.

171
00:07:37,375 --> 00:07:39,333
E-class has its
share of good points.

172
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:40,250
[TAKEBAYASHI]
Huh.

173
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:41,583
That's hilarious.

174
00:07:41,666 --> 00:07:43,041
You idiots have even less
screen time than I do.

175
00:07:43,125 --> 00:07:45,375
[KIMURA, SUGAYA scream]

176
00:07:45,458 --> 00:07:48,000
And yet you... still
got your chocolate!

177
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:50,000
That's your biggest issue?

178
00:07:51,666 --> 00:07:54,125
As a class, we are more
than the sum of our parts.

179
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:56,041
[TAKEBAYASHI] You're still
the imposter, aren't you?

180
00:07:57,666 --> 00:07:59,541
[MAEHARA] There's just no
getting through to him.

181
00:07:59,625 --> 00:08:01,083
[ISOGAI] Anyone figured
out why the teachers

182
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:02,750
haven't bothered to show up yet?

183
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:04,125
[MEG]
This is hopeless.

184
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:05,208
[RITSU]
No, it's not!

185
00:08:05,291 --> 00:08:07,125
Give me a chance
to turn this around.

186
00:08:07,208 --> 00:08:08,458
[NAKAMURA]
Ritsu?

187
00:08:08,541 --> 00:08:10,208
Ever since joining E-class,
I've made it a point

188
00:08:10,291 --> 00:08:12,541
of closely monitoring
our development.

189
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:13,958
If there's one thing
I'm certain of,

190
00:08:14,041 --> 00:08:16,208
it's that we can only
succeed as a team.

191
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:18,083
Friends with the same goal.

192
00:08:18,166 --> 00:08:20,250
Please standby while
I calculate the best way

193
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:23,458
of getting Takebayashi
back on board.

194
00:08:23,541 --> 00:08:27,208
Ah. Yes. I'll simply
use my magic.

195
00:08:27,291 --> 00:08:28,250
Okay.

196
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:30,250
I'm picking up
some serious power!

197
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:32,083
[RITSU]
Takebayashi?

198
00:08:33,916 --> 00:08:37,625
Stay with us, please.
We need you.

199
00:08:37,708 --> 00:08:39,833
[gasps]

200
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:41,875
[CLASS]
Takebayashi!

201
00:08:44,875 --> 00:08:46,625
Um, what just happened?

202
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:47,875
[RITSU]
Sorcery.

203
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:49,208
No, but really.

204
00:08:49,291 --> 00:08:50,625
[RITSU]
Sorcery.

205
00:08:50,708 --> 00:08:52,791
Hey! What are you eating?!

206
00:08:57,250 --> 00:08:59,666
Just don't sweat the
small stuff, you know?

207
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:02,458
It's hard to be uptight when
you've seen what I have.

208
00:09:02,541 --> 00:09:04,750
Name of the game
is chill, trust me.

209
00:09:06,625 --> 00:09:08,875
Life is too short.

210
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:10,291
[TAKABAYASHI sighs]

211
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:12,458
Anyway, if you still want
me to be part of the team,

212
00:09:12,541 --> 00:09:13,750
I s'pose I'm game.

213
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:15,500
[ISOGAI]
I, uh, don't quite understand

214
00:09:15,583 --> 00:09:16,541
what changed your mind,

215
00:09:16,625 --> 00:09:18,291
but you're sticking
around, so...

216
00:09:18,375 --> 00:09:20,583
[MEG] What kind of magic
did you use exactly?

217
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:22,416
[RITSU]
It's a secret.

218
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:25,333
♪ As the seasons come... ♪

219
00:09:25,416 --> 00:09:27,583
[NAGISA]
He's singing?

220
00:09:27,666 --> 00:09:31,708
♪ My true love disappears
behind a cloud. ♪

221
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:37,000
♪ Like the sun 'cause that's
the way of new beginnings. ♪

222
00:09:37,083 --> 00:09:39,625
♪ Let's take it slow. ♪

223
00:09:39,708 --> 00:09:44,083
♪ Until the day I see
you in a crowd. ♪

224
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:47,875
♪ And mem'ry sings what
could have been. ♪

225
00:09:47,958 --> 00:09:56,416
♪ Until the day when our
hearts will meet again. ♪

